column5: Does anyone have a replica of a fish they caught? I caught a 32.5 in walleye on the weekend and am considering getting one made. Also is there anyone in the area of SW Ont that does a really good job of this?  I have a good bunch of pics of the fish.  Can't seem to figure out how to put one up though Thanks
Replicas are usually made out of fiberglass, Advance texidermy is the best IMO
Yes 100% advanced taxidermy I have a 54" musky and 27" pickerel done by them
Tybo and Joey had one done by Advance. It is simply awesome.  You will pay. But  you,ll be paying for quality work.  Nice fish.
I have a 45 inch pike by advanced, a 55 inch muskie by advanced and two 15 inch perch by advanced.  I am very happy with them all.
What a beast of a fish!!!  Great Job Lakerguy!
Solid walleye. That is a pig.

Nice walleye indeed. Great catch.  I also highly recommend Advanced Taxidermy. Their fish replicas look like they're alive. I have a 37-inch steelhead they did for me almost 15 years ago ... it still looks like I just slid it up the bank. And the stuff they do now is even better!
Thanks guys Put the order in with Advanced Should look great above our fireplace
